The paper deals with the self-assembly of complex structures using the Tile Assembly Model, which is a topic in computational geometry and discrete mathematics (cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.CG). The Sierpinski triangle is a well-known fractal structure, which is also studied in graph theory and combinatorics (cs.GT). The paper also involves analyzing the fractal dimension of the self-assembled structures, which is a topic in machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.LG).
